Direct Known Subclasses:
Fish
public abstract class MarineHerbivore extends Herbivore
The MarineHerbivore class represents a marine herbivore species in the ecosystem. This class extends the Herbivore class and adds marine-specific behaviors such as swimming. Marine herbivores are typically creatures that consume plants in the ocean.

  • Constructor Details

    • MarineHerbivore

      public MarineHerbivore(String name, int energy, Positionn positionn, Environment environment, int vitesse, javafx.scene.image.ImageView imageView)
      Constructs a new MarineHerbivore with the specified attributes. Marine herbivores generally don't have a grouping instinct, which is why it is set to false by default.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the marine herbivore.
      energy - The initial energy of the marine herbivore.
      positionn - The position of the marine herbivore in the ecosystem.
      environment - The environment where the marine herbivore resides.
      vitesse - The speed of the marine herbivore.
      imageView - The image representation of the marine herbivore.
